      {
        "id": 2325616,
        "name": "Peter Moy",
        "username": "P_Moy",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/a9a28c/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-29T19:36:21.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Home to New York for the holidays to see family and to have two spectacular dinners with my burg loving brother.  Because of the wines, we decided to drink only 2 bottles per dinner among four of us to savor and truly appreciate what was in the glass.  We kept the food simple so that it would enhance the wines.  We were glad we did.</p>\n<p>1988 Pol Roger Sir Winston Churchill - Beautiful gold color.  Fine mousse that did not dissipate over the two hours the bottle was drunk.<br>\nIntense and complex nose of citrus, dough, yeast, nuts, flowers, honey and apricot.  Aromas are incredibly focused.  Elegant and concentrated, with great acidity.  Fills the mouth with citrus and honey flavors.  Long finish, with a slight oxidative and saline note adding to its complexity.  SWC is my favorite champagne, and this bottle was the best of seven drunk so far.</p>\n<p>1964 Rousseau Chambertin - Bricking throughout.  Ethereal bouquet of damp earth, truffles, spice, and hints of dark fruits and game.  The perfume can only be Burgundy, and was mesmerizing to smell.  Please don\u2019t wake me up.  Medium bodied and elegant, with subtle tastes of dark fruit and earth that stain the palate.  Silky, sensuous texture and long finish.  Impeccable balance.  Was everything one expects in a great bottle of Burgundy, and more.  Served with grilled duck breast lightly sauced with a reduction of red wine, butter and chopped black truffles.</p>\n<p>2006 Deutz Amour de Deutz Blanc de Blancs - Yellow color with fine bubbles.  Enticing aromas of dough, apples, nuts, flowers, minerals and caramel.  Citrus and apples on the palate carried by fine acidity.  Taste lingers.  Really fresh and delicious, the kind of champagne one can drink all day.</p>\n<p>1949 Maison Leroy Chambertin - Deep mature color.  Haunting perfume of sous bois, mushrooms, crushed leaves, and the barest trace of dark fruit.  Some gamy notes emerge with swirling.  This glides across the palate revealing tastes of violets and dark fruit.  As silky as a Hermes scarf.  Medium to long finish, and in complete balance.  If this was powerful in its youth, it has evolved into a wine of elegance and purity.  A joy to drink.  Served with grilled venison.</p>",
